    "history" -> {"12", "14.0", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {"Dicke model"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Symbol", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> "QuantumMob/Q3",
     "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "DickeBasis[s1, s2, ..., {m, n}] returns the computational basis for a \
system Flatten[{s1, s2, ...}] of qubits and/or qudits and bosons, where the \
number of particles in each bosonic mode is limited in Range[m, n]. \
DickeBasis[spec, n] is equivalent to DickeBasis[spec, {m, n}], where m is the \
maximum of the Bottom values of the bosonic modes. DickeBasis[spec] is \
equivalent to DickeBasis[spec, {m, n}], where m is the maximum of the Bottom \
values of the bosonic modes and n is the minimum of the Top values of bosonic \
modes.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> "DickeBasis", 
    "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", "windowtitle" -> 
